  "articleSummary": "The article argues that AngularJS v1.x is powerful but frequently overused, leading to performance degradation from excessive `$watch` instances, bloated `$scope` hierarchies, and directive sprawl. It offers a tutorial-style guide with practical tips: limit directive nesting, use one-way binding (`{::}}`), avoid directives inside `ng-repeat`, and leverage Browserify for project organization. The tone is critical yet constructive, framing overuse as \"OVER-Angular.JSification\" and using metaphors like \"2-way sword\" and the \"hammer/nail\" adage. The intended audience is AngularJS developers building medium-to-large applications who need to optimize performance and consider alternatives like React or Polymer.",
